{"id": "EUVD-2023-59838", "enisaUuid": "af0e06ad-43d0-35d3-92b8-8aeb6c4565cf", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncifs: fix DFS traversal oops without CONFIG_CIFS_DFS_UPCALL\n\nWhen compiled with CONFIG_CIFS_DFS_UPCALL disabled, cifs_dfs_d_automount\nis NULL. cifs.ko logic for mapping CIFS_FATTR_DFS_REFERRAL attributes to\nS_AUTOMOUNT and corresponding dentry flags is retained regardless of\nCONFIG_CIFS_DFS_UPCALL, leading to a NULL pointer dereference in\nVFS follow_automount() when traversing a DFS referral link:\n  BUG: kernel NULL pointer dereference, address: 0000000000000000\n  ...\n  Call Trace:\n   <TASK>\n   __traverse_mounts+0xb5/0x220\n   ? cifs_revalidate_mapping+0x65/0xc0 [cifs]\n   step_into+0x195/0x610\n   ? lookup_fast+0xe2/0xf0\n   path_lookupat+0x64/0x140\n   filename_lookup+0xc2/0x140\n   ? __create_object+0x299/0x380\n   ? kmem_cache_alloc+0x119/0x220\n   ? user_path_at_empty+0x31/0x50\n   user_path_at_empty+0x31/0x50\n   __x64_sys_chdir+0x2a/0xd0\n   ? exit_to_user_mode_prepare+0xca/0x100\n   do_syscall_64+0x42/0x90\n   entry_SYSCALL_64_after_hwframe+0x72/0xdc\n\nThis fix adds an inline cifs_dfs_d_automount() {return -EREMOTE} handler\nwhen CONFIG_CIFS_DFS_UPCALL is disabled. An alternative would be to\navoid flagging S_AUTOMOUNT, etc. without CONFIG_CIFS_DFS_UPCALL. This\napproach was chosen as it provides more control over the error path.", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:29", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-03T21:31:00", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8cd7dbc9c46d51e00a0a8372e07cc1cbb8d24a77", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8afb1fabcec1929db46977e84baeee0cc0e79242", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/657d7c215ca974d366ab1808213f716e1e3aa950", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/26a32a212bc540f4773cd6af8cf73e967d72569c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b64305185b76f1d5145ce594ff48f3f0e70695bd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b7d854c33ab48e55fc233699bbefe39ec9bb5c05", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1e144b68208e98fd4602c842a7149ba5f41d87fb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/179a88a8558bbf42991d361595281f3e45d7edfc", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53246"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53246"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "14f418c4-64e9-3002-8015-78d0eb1271f4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.14.312"}, {"id": "1e2ec8d8-db91-32f2-b548-c957f16e9eb1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <b7d854c33ab48e55fc233699bbefe39ec9bb5c05"}, {"id": "2078280b-258f-35db-9df6-bdad5f4fafb4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.106"}, {"id": "218c1691-3140-39e7-ad7b-f57cebaf5416", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <1e144b68208e98fd4602c842a7149ba5f41d87fb"}, {"id": "61269870-1bd0-30cc-b942-656131010c43", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.4.240"}, {"id": "82a1892a-d889-3a52-bfa4-a1a1a15f16b1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2.10"}, {"id": "84a19192-2e06-3fc1-945e-6034f21fdbca", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <179a88a8558bbf42991d361595281f3e45d7edfc"}, {"id": "8586296a-c419-30d2-b01f-abde536238f6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <8cd7dbc9c46d51e00a0a8372e07cc1cbb8d24a77"}, {"id": "88dcad1c-5005-326c-b706-04ee0c64e77c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <657d7c215ca974d366ab1808213f716e1e3aa950"}, {"id": "898da74c-3fb5-38cf-843b-8d9ced4d795a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <b64305185b76f1d5145ce594ff48f3f0e70695bd"}, {"id": "8af8ebd2-bb32-3657-8a81-d7fcf6c876c5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.177"}, {"id": "9de8e4a7-fbc7-3d8f-bd2e